beer.beer_description:
This Düsseldorf Altbier is a take on the traditional style of beer from the old town. "Alt" refers to the "old" style of brewing (i.e. making top-fermented ales) that was common before lager brewing became popular. Using a base malt of Pale, Biscuit, Brown, and Chocolate Malt. A slight nuttiness and small amount of integrated roast character gives a malty start with a dry finish. Combined with a traditional Kölsch yeast that gives off subtly citrus, pear, and dark cherry.

Pairs well with a soft white pretzel.
